         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">21/9/81 ¶  ¶ It affords me much pleasure, dear Sir Joseph, to introduce to you Mr Howitz, a Danish Gentleman, who for a series of years lived in Melbourne, but returned to Europe with his family last ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.09.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-81, f. 326.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">21/9/81<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Hooker: ' And' [Answered].</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It affords me much pleasure, dear Sir Joseph, to introduce to you Mr Howitz, a Danish Gentleman, who for a series of years lived in Melbourne, but returned to Europe with his family last year.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Howitz is an accomplished mathematician, a splendid draughtsman, and he went also through a forestral education; irrespective of this he is a good linguist. Perhaps it is within your power to advance the interest of this deserving Gentleman. His Lady, a native of Melbourne, is very accomplished in vocal music, and a young family is dependent on their exertions. I was quite befriended with Mr Howitz, when he was here.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir Joseph Hooker,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">C.B., K.C.S.L, V.P.R.S &amp; L.S,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Director of the Royal</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">botanic Garden of</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Kew<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>D. Howitz did not use the letter of introduction until 18 October 1882, when he wrote to J. Hooker from 58 Guilford St. Russell Square London W.C. (f. 327):</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.0016in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Sir Joseph Hooker</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.0016in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">C. B. &amp;c &amp;c</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.0016in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Sir!</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.6665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">I beg to enclose letter of introduction from Baron von Mueller, which I have had no occasion to present before now, and to beg You to grant me an interview.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.3209in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">I remain Sir,</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.6555in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Your most obedient servant</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.8138in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">D Howitz</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 2.1484in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Forest conservator.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.6693in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by Hooker: 'Asked to fix a day | called Nov 8/82'.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.6681in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">There is a subsequent undated letter from D. Howitz to Hooker (f. 328):</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.0016in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Dear Sir!</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.6665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">I beg to thank you for your kind note and to state that I will take the liberty of calling on you on Wednesday between 2 and 2 1/2 at Kew if you should not prefer seeing me in town on Thursday</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.3209in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">I have the honor to remain</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.6555in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.8138in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">Your most obedient servant</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 2.1484in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">D Howitz | F.C.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.6681in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">MS annotation by Hooker</seg>: Called Wanted [temporary] employment as artist'.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 1.0016in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 1 January 1883 (in this edition as 83-01-01c).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
